net.kreatious.pianoleopard.intervalset

Class IntervalSet<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.kreatious.pianoleopard.intervalset.IntervalSet<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of mapped values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<V>

    public class IntervalSet<V>
extends Object
implements Iterable<V>
    An ordered tree data structure for holding intervals. The user can efficiently find all intervals that overlap with a given interval or point.

    Interval sets are optimized for being queried far more often than they are modified.

    This set does not support null keys or values, but does support duplicate intervals.

    Author:
    Jay-R Studer

      • put

        public Optional<V> put(long low,
                       long high,
                       V value)
        Associates the specified interval with the specified value in this set. If this set previously contained a mapping for the interval, the old value is replaced. If the specified interval is invalid, nothing is inserted.
        Parameters:
        low - the low end of the range the specified value to associate
        high - the high end of the range the specified value to associate
        value - value to be associated with the specified key
        Returns:
        the previous value associated with the interval, or empty if there was no mapping for the interval.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the specified key or value is null

      • removeFirst

        public Optional<V> removeFirst(long low,
                               long high,
                               Predicate<? super V> criteria)
        Removes the first value for the specified interval from this set that matches the given criteria.
        Parameters:
        low - the low end of the range the specified value to associate
        high - the high end of the range the specified value to associate
        criteria - the value to delete
        Returns:
        the removed value, or empty if no value was removed
        Throws:

      • subSet

        public Iterable<V> subSet(long low,
                          long high)
        Returns an iterable read only view of the values in this set that overlaps the specified interval. If low and high are equal, the returned view contains the intervals containing a single point.
        Parameters:
        low - low portion of the interval to retrieve
        high - high portion of the interval to retrieve
        Returns:
        a read only view of the portion of this set overlapping the specified interval.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if low is greater than high
